The paper proposes a method for denoising optical coherence tomography (OCT) images using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as well as information theory (cs.IT) since the paper deals with noise reduction. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-input networks, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the learning of parameters, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
